ETexas%20leads%20the%20nation%20in%20wind-generated%20power%20and%20is%20third%20in%20the%20country%20for%20solar%20power.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20heat%20is%20inescapable%20in%20the%20Lone%20Star%20state%20this%20summer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAustin%20has%20hit%20triple-digit%20temperatures%20for%2034%20days%20straight.%20El%20Paso%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20seen%2056%20triple-digit%20days%20this%20summer%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FNWSElPaso%2Fstatus%2F1689961821690818560%5C%22%3Ethird-highest%20frequency%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20state's%20history.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20these%20extreme%20temperatures%20continue%20to%20bake%20Texas%2C%20residents%20are%20cranking%20up%20their%20air%20conditioning%2C%20straining%20the%20state's%20power%20grid.%20As%20of%20August%2012%2C%20Texas%20has%20broken%2010%20all-time%20peak%20power%20demand%20records%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ercot.com%2Fstatic-assets%2Fdata%2Fnews%2FContent%2Fa-peak-demand%2F2023%2Fall-time-records.htm%5C%22%3Edata%20from%20the%20Electric%20Reliability%20Council%20of%20Texas%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20organization%20that%20operates%C2%A090%25%20of%20the%20state's%20electric%20load.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20grid%20has%20held%20up%20remarkably%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Emily%20Foxhall%2C%20an%20energy%20reporter%20for%20the%20Texas%20Tribune%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fvideo%2Ftexas-energy-prices-skyrocket-amid-summer-heat%2F%5C%22%3Etold%20CBS.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20resilience%20is%20thanks%20to%20the%20state's%20reliance%20on%20renewable%20energy%2C%20Foxhall%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%20produces%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcomptroller.texas.gov%2Feconomy%2Ffiscal-notes%2F2022%2Fsep%2Fenergy.php%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFor%2520the%2520last%2520decade%2520and%2Csolar%252Dgeneration%2520potential%2520as%2520well.%5C%22%3Emore%20wind-powered%20electricity%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20any%20other%20state%20and%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Feere%2Fsolar%2Fquarterly-solar-industry-update%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enational%20leader%20in%20solar%20energy%3C%2Fa%3E%20alongside%20California%20and%20Florida.%20Texas%20is%20also%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Farticles%2Fdoe-report-finds-clean-energy-jobs-grew-every-state-2022%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethird%20in%20the%20nation%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20clean%20energy%20job%20growth%2C%20adding%205%2C100%20jobs%20in%202022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoshua%20Rhodes%2C%20a%20research%20scientist%20with%20the%20Webber%20Energy%20Group%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20solar%20power%20has%20proven%20especially%20key%20this%20summer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20twice%20as%20much%20solar%20as%20we%20had%20last%20year%2C%20and%20so%20the%20same%20sun%20that's%20heating%20up%20all%20the%20buildings%20and%20driving%20the%20air%20conditioning%20use%20is%20making%20electricity%2C%26quot%3B%20Rhodes%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BNot%20only%20are%20we%20setting%20demand%20records%2C%20but%20we're%20also%20setting%20solar%20demand%20records%20simultaneously.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2010%2C%20wind%20and%20solar%20energy%20generated%2024.69%25%20of%20the%20needed%20energy%20during%20the%20state's%20peak%20hour%20of%20power%20usage%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ercot.com%2Fmp%2Fdata-products%2Fdata-product-details%3Fid%3DNP4-760-ER%5C%22%3Edata%20from%20the%20Electric%20Reliability%20Council%20of%20Texas%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20growing%20penetration%20of%20new%2C%20variable%20renewables%20displacing%20conventional%20dispatchable%20generation%20for%20power%2C%20we'll%20need%20to%20rely%20more%20on%20renewables%20during%20peak%20conditions%20than%20we%20ever%20have%20before%2C%26quot%3B