up.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20single-use%20drones%2C%20called%20Geran-2%2C%20appear%20to%20be%20Russian-made%20versions%20of%20the%20Iranian%20drones%2C%20the%20researchers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20forces%20began%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firanian-suicide-kamikaze-drones-russia-uses-ukraine-cities-explainer-2022-10%5C%22%3Eusing%20Iranian-made%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20strike%20cities%20across%20Ukraine%20last%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20small%2C%20propellor-driven%20weapons%20can%20be%20packed%20with%20explosives%20that%20detonate%20upon%20impact%2C%20which%20is%20why%20they%20are%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20%26quot%3Bkamikaze%26quot%3B%20drones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20new%20version%20will%20allow%20Russia%20to%20sustain%20its%20attack%20patterns%20and%20its%20reliance%20on%20these%20one-way%20drones%2C%26quot%3B%20Damien%20Spleeters%2C%20who%20led%20the%20group's%20investigation%2C%20told%20The%20Times.%20%26quot%3BSo%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20make%20it%20domestically%20will%20allow%20them%20to%20continue%20to%20rely%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Geran-2%20drones%20are%20built%20with%20different%20materials%20to%20the%20Shahed%2C%20and%20they%20also%20appear%20to%20have%20been%20adapted%20to%20better%20suit%20Russian%20needs%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20drones%20are%20made%20with%20fiberglass%20over%20layers%20of%20woven%20carbon%20fiber%2C%20which%20is%20different%20from%20the%20honeycomb%20type%20of%20material%20used%20in%20the%20Iranian%20drones%2C%20The%20Times%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20drones%20that%20Conflict%20Armament%20Research%20inspected%20also%20contained%20electronic%20modules%20called%20Kometa%20in%20their%20guidance%20sections%20%E2%80%94%20these%20have%20previously%20been%20found%20in%20Russian%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20news%20outlets%20also%20published%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdefence-ua.com%2Fweapon_and_tech%2Fchim_novij_dron_kamikadze_shahed_vidriznjajetsja_vid_staroji_versiji_pjat_golovnih_vidminnostej-12261.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ephotos%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20drones%20that%20they%20say%20appear%20to%20have%20been%20made%20in%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223321%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20explosion%20of%20a%20drone%20is%20seen%20in%20the%20sky%20over%20the%20city%20during%20a%20Russian%20drone%20strike%2C%20amid%20Russia's%20attack%20on%20Ukraine%2C%20in%20Kyiv%2C%20Ukraine%20May%204%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d75f035e5d5a00195ccd0b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222491%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20explosion%20of%20a%20drone%20is%20seen%20in%20the%20sky%20over%20the%20city%20during%20a%20Russian%20drone%20strike%2C%20amid%20Russia's%20attack%20on%20Ukraine%2C%20in%20Kyiv%2C%20Ukraine%20May%204%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FGleb%20Garanich%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESamuel%20Bendett%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20Russian%20military%20drones%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Naval%20Analyses%2C%20told%20The%20Times%20that%20analysts%20have%20been%20waiting%20to%20see%20if%20Russia%20could%20make%20its%20own%20versions%20of%20the%20Iranian%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20now%20seen%20in%20Russian%20media%20that%20these%20are%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20domestic%20assembly%2C%20and%20there%20are%20changes%20introduced%20in%20the%20design%20based%20on%20their%20own%20needs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20indicative%20of%20Russians%20trying%20to%20come%20up%20with%20a%20drone%20that's%20just%20as%20capable%20as%20the%20original%20Shahed%20that%20could%20then%20be%20scaled%20up%20in%20significant%20quantities%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ultimate%20goal%20for%20them%20is%20to%20maintain%20the%20capacity%20while%20making%20them%20more%20effective%20and%20actually%20driving%20down%20the%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Russia%20began%20its%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20Western%20states%20imposed%20strict%20sanctions%20to%20curtail%20Russia's%20access%20to%20foreign-made%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Russia%20has%20continued%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-66452100%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacquire%20many%20of%20the%20military%20supplies%20it%20needs.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20findings%20also%20raise%20questions%20about%20export%20control%20and%20counter-diversion%20measures%2C%20as%20we%20see%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20components%20we%20found%20are%20made%20after%20February%202022%2C%26quot%3B%20Spleeters%20told%20The%20Times.%20%26quot%3BSo%20if%20they%20can%20keep%20on%20getting%20them%2C%20there's%20an%20issue%2C%20obviously.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-making-own-versions-iranian-attack-drones-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691836575000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6356c3b6390dfe00196da634%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-making-own-versions-iranian-attack-drones-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Geran-2%20drone%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20Russian-made%20version%20of%20Iran's%20Shahed-136%20attack%20drone%20widely%20used%20against%20Ukraine%2C%20a%20New%20York%20Times%20report%20says.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ashoaib%40insider.com%20(Alia%20Shoaib)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-making-own-versions-iranian-attack-drones-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amid%20China's%20'Objection'%2C%20India%20Defends%20Use%20of%20'Vasudhaiva%20Kutumbakam'%20Phrase%20in%20G20%20Documents%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04141303%2FFjHNMmeakAEkbxa.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EIndia%20has%20defended%20the%20use%20of%20the%20Sanskrit%20phrase%20%3Cem%3EVasudhaiva%20Kutumbakam%3C%2Fem%3E%20(the%20world%20is%20one%20family)%20in%20the%20G20%20logo%20and%20letterhead%20of%20each%20document%20after%20reports%20emerged%20that%20China%20apparently%20objected%20to%20the%20use%20of%20non-English%20language%20in%20G20%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20also%20clarified%20that%20it%20uses%20only%20the%20%E2%80%9CEnglish%20version%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9COne%20Earth%2C%20One%20Family%2C%20One%20Future%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20in%20its%20summary%20documents%20and%20outcome%20statements%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fcentre-defends-use-of-vasudhaiva-kutumbakam-in-g-20-as-china-raises-objections%2Farticle67184856.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20you%20are%20aware%2C%20the%20theme%20of%20the%20G20%20Presidency%20in%20English%20is%20%E2%80%98One%20Earth%20One%20Family%20One%20Future%E2%80%99.%20This%20is%20based%20on%20our%20civilisational%20ethos%20of%20Vasudhaiva%20Kutumbakam%20which%20has%20received%20widespread%20support%20and%20permeates%20many%20of%20the%20initiatives%20that%20India%20has%20brought%20to%20the%20G20%20Agenda%20and%20this%20also%20finds%20a%20mention%20in%20the%20G20%20logo%20which%20has%20the%20verse%20in%20Sanskrit%20and%20English%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%20spokesperson%20Arindam%20Bagchi%20on%20Friday%2C%20August%2011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApparently%2C%20China%20was%20reluctant%20to%20accept%20the%20usage%20of%20the%20Sanskrit%20phrase%20in%20the%20outcome%20document%20after%20the%20G20%20Energy%20Transitions%20Working%20Group%20meeting%20held%20in%20Goa%20on%20July%2020.%20China%20is%20said%20to%20have%20raised%20the%20point%20that%20Sanskrit%20cannot%20be%20used%2C%20for%20it%20is%20not%20recognised%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%20as%20an%20official%20language.%20The%20global%20body%20considers%20only%20Arabic%2C%20Chinese%2C%20English%2C%20French%2C%20Russian%2C%20and%20Spanish%20as%20its%20official%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fnation%2F2023%2Faug%2F11%2Famid-chinas-objection-to-vasudhaiva-kutumbakam-india-says-its-the-inspiration-for-g20-theme-2604335.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20China%20was%20the%20only%20one%20to%20raise%20objections%20while%20other%20member%20states%20saw%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20it.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20others%20reportedly%20argued%20that%20India%20as%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20G20%20had%20the%20right%20to%20take%20a%20call%20on%20such%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20diplomatic%20sources%2C%20Chinese%20and%20Indian%20negotiators%20have%20been%20wrangling%20over%20the%20past%20few%20weeks%20with%20the%20former%20taking%20a%20%E2%80%9Cconfrontational%20stance%20over%20several%20phrases%20introduced%20by%20the%20Indian%20G-20%20Sherpa%20team%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20sticking%20points%20are%20the%20language%20used%20for%20the%20promotion%20of%20millets%20such%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CLifestyle%20for%20Environment%E2%80%9D%20(LiFE)%20initiative%2C%20proposed%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20and%20even%20terms%20like%20%E2%80%9Cgender-led%20development%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Chinese%20delegation%20alleged%20that%20such%20language%20amounted%20to%20supplanting%20UN-agreed%20language%20for%20Sustainable%20Development%20G