Url%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66484635.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Unusual%20Case%20Of%20'Blue%20Legs'%20In%20Long%20Covid%20Patient%20Seen%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAn%20unusual%20case%20of%20a%20long%20Covid%20patient's%20legs%20turning%20blue%20after%2010%20minutes%20of%20standing%20has%20been%20reported%20in%20a%20study%20published%20in%20The%20Lancet%20journal.%20The%20study%20described%20the%20case%20of%20a%2033-year%20old%20man%20who%20developed%20a%20condition%20called%20acrocyanosis%2C%20which%20refers%20to%20blood%20pooling%20in%20the%20veins%20of%20the%20legs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20minute%20after%20standing%2C%20his%20legs%20began%20to%20redden%20and%20became%20increasingly%20blue%20over%20time%2C%20with%20the%20veins%20becoming%20more%20prominent%2C%20the%20study%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Leeds%2C%20UK%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20colour%20was%20seen%20to%20become%20much%20more%20pronounced%20after%2010%20minutes%20of%20standing%2C%20with%20the%20patient%20describing%20a%20heavy%2C%20itchy%20sensation%20in%20his%20legs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20his%20original%20colour%20was%20observed%20to%20return%20two%20minutes%20after%20he%20resumed%20a%20non-standing%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20patient%20said%20he%20had%20started%20to%20experience%20the%20discolouration%20since%20his%20COVID-19%20infection%2C%20the%20researchers%20said%20in%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20a%20striking%20case%20of%20acrocyanosis%20in%20a%20patient%20who%20had%20not%20experienced%20it%20before%20his%20COVID-19%20infection%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Manoj%20Sivan%2C%20the%20study's%20author%20and%20associate%20clinical%20professor%20at%20the%20university's%20School%20of%20Medicine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20patient%20was%20then%20diagnosed%20with%20postural%20orthostatic%20tachycardia%20syndrome%20(POTS)%2C%20a%20condition%20causing%20an%20abnormal%20increase%20in%20heart%20rate%20upon%20standing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELong%20Covid%20has%20been%20shown%20to%20affect%20multiple%20systems%20in%20the%20body%2C%20including%20the%20autonomic%20nervous%20system%2C%20which%20is%20responsible%20for%20regulating%20involuntary%20processes%20in%20the%20body%20such%20as%20heart%20rate%2C%20blood%20pressure%2C%20respiration%2C%20digestion%2C%20and%20sexual%20arousal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcrocyanosis%20has%20previously%20been%20observed%20in%20children%20with%20dysfunction%20of%20the%20autonomic%20nervous%20system%20(dysautonomia)%2C%20a%20common%20symptom%20of%20post-viral%20syndromes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPatients%20experiencing%20this%20may%20not%20be%20aware%20that%20it%20can%20be%20a%20symptom%20of%20long%20COVID%20and%20dysautonomia%20and%20may%20feel%20concerned%20about%20what%20they%20are%20seeing.%20Similarly%2C%20clinicians%20may%20not%20be%20aware%20of%20the%20link%20between%20acrocyanosis%20and%20long%20Covid%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sivan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrevious%20research%20by%20Sivan's%20team%20has%20shown%20that%20both%20dysautonomia%20and%20POTS%20frequently%20develop%20in%20people%20with%20Long%20Covid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDysautonomia%20is%20also%20seen%20in%20a%20number%20of%20other%20long-term%20conditions%2C%20such%20as%20Fibromyalgia%20and%20Myalgic%20Encephalomyelitis%2C%20also%20known%20as%20Chronic%20Fatigue%20Syndrome%20or%20ME%2C%20both%20of%20which%20affect%20muscles%20and%20cause%20pain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20said%20that%20the%20patient's%20case%20highlighted%20the%20need%20for%20greater%20awareness%20of%20this%20symptom%20among%20people%20experiencing%20this%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20ensure%20that%20there%20is%20more%20awareness%20of%20dysautonomia%20in%20long%20Covid%20so%20that%20clinicians%20have%20the%20tools%20they%20need%20to%20manage%20patients%20appropriately%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sivan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELong%20Covid%20includes%20symptoms%20of%20fa