omebuyers.%20Higher%20borrowing%20costs%20have%20limited%20the%20amount%20of%20homeowners%20looking%20to%20sell%2C%20given%20they%20feel%20like%20they're%20locked%20into%20their%20current%20low-mortgage%20rate.%20That's%20squeezed%20the%20supply%20of%20homes%20available%20for%20sale%20on%20the%20market%2C%20driving%20up%20prices%20for%20those%20looking%20to%20buy%20a%20property%20for%20the%20first%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGas%20prices%20U-turn%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20months%2C%20drivers%20have%20enjoyed%20the%20lowest%20gas%20prices%20since%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20broke%20out.%20But%20now%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Fus-gas-prices-oil-inflation-smile-mohamed-el-erian-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethose%20costs%20have%20taken%20a%20U-turn%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20gallon%20of%20gas%20traded%20at%20%243.83%2C%20its%20highest%20level%20since%20October%202022%2C%20per%20AAA.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20largely%20because%20of%20%26quot%3Bgreedflation%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20oil%20suppliers%20including%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20Russia%20cut%20production%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20lift%20crude%20prices.%20Both%20benchmark%20Brent%20crude%20and%20West%20Texas%20Intermediate%20are%20currently%20trading%20upwards%20of%20%2480%20a%20barrel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20threatened%20to%20worsen%20the%20inflation%20problem%20in%20the%20US%20that%20the%20Fed%20has%20worked%20so%20hard%20to%20kill%20in%20what%20would%20be%20another%20blow%20to%20consumers'%20wallets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFoodflation%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20glass%20of%20orange%20juice%20to%20a%20piece%20of%20chocolate%2C%20buying%20groceries%20is%20also%20hurting%20consumers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20after%20a%20spike%20in%20orange%20juice%20prices%2C%20cocoa%20costs%20surged%20to%20a%20multi-year%20high%20%E2%80%93%20both%20surges%20coming%20on%20the%20back%20of%20crop