n%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20yet%20another%20form%20of%20Hindi%20imposition.%20South%20Indian%20lawyers%20are%20going%20to%20spend%20most%20of%20the%20time%20in%20courts%20trying%20to%20pronounce%20these%20names.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Ci%20data-stringify-type%3D%5C%22italic%5C%22%3EThe%20Wire%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3ESanjoy%20Ghose%2C%20senior%20advocate%20in%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20said%20that%20this%20is%20%E2%80%9Cunheard%20of.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20legislations%2C%20in%20the%20form%20of%20ordinances%20or%20bills%20have%20a%20Hindi%20and%20an%20English%20version.%20But%20this%20is%20for%20the%20first%20time%20that%20they%20have%20given%20the%20English%20version%20a%20Hindi%20name%20and%20forced%20a%20Hindi%20name%20on%20English%20law.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20this%20also%20needs%20to%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20light%20of%20a%20very%20Brahmincal%20Hindi%20imposition%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20reason%20I%20say%20this%20is%20that%20is%20a%20very%20Sanskritised%20Hindi%20name%20that%20they%20have%20given%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20it%20could%20have%20been%20named%20simply%20%3Ci%20data-stringify-type%3D%5C%22italic%5C%22%3EBharatiya%20Danda%20Kosh%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Efor%20instance%20but%20instead%20it%20is%20called%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%2C%20which%20is%20a%20very%20Sanskritised%20Hindi%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhose%20added%20that%20it%20is%20also%20not%20clear%20why%20there%20was%20a%20need%20to%20bring%20in%20entirely%20new%20laws%20instead%20of%20simply%20bringing%20in%20amendments.%E2%80%9CYes%2C%20these%20are%20colonial%20legislations.%20But%20other%20nations%20like%20Malaysia%2C%20Singapore%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20etc.%2C%20have%20also%20continued%20with%20the%20same%20penal%20code.%20Why%20is%20there%20a%20need%20to%20replace%20it%20entirely%20instead%20of%20bringing%20in%20amendments%3F%E2%80%9DAshwani%20Kumar%2C%20senior%20advocate%20and%20former%20Union%20minister%20for%20Law%20and%20Justice%20said%20that%20the%20changes%20in%20the%20law%20%E2%80%9Cwere%20prompted%20by%20judgments%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20Government%E2%80%99s%20appreciation%20of%20their%20need.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20changes%20in%20law%20relating%20to%20sedition%2C%20mob%20lynching%20and%20crimes%20against%20minors%20and%20women%20are%20welcome%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20comprehensive%20law%20against%20custodial%20torture%20to%20address%20its%20several%20dimensions%20is%20not%20understandable.%20Hopefully%2C%20such%20a%20law%20will%20be%20introduced%20soon%20in%20furtherance%20of%20the%20right%20to%20dignity%20guaranteed%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691760169000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F09222428%2FAmit-Anil-Chandra-Shah-in-Lok-Sabha.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsedition-law-repealed-three-new-bills-tabled-in-parliament-to-replace-criminal-laws%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Although%20Amit%20Shah%20said%20sedition%20law%20has%20been%20'repealed'%2C%20it%20appears%20only%20the%20word%20'sedition'%20may%20have%20been%20dropped%2C%20for%20the%20law%20remains%20and%2C%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20has%20been%20made%20more%20draconian.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsedition-law-repealed-three-new-bills-tabled-in-parliament-to-replace-criminal-laws%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22K2%3A%20Climbers%20deny%20walking%20by%20dying%20guide%20in%20bid%20to%20break%20record%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691758251000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FC37F%2Fproduction%2F_130774005_summit.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2